{"key":"post-13727557","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>13727557</id>\n<content>You need to mist.&amp;nbsp; &lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;It's extremely important for moisture to be evaporating from the substrate, as this is the number 1 pinning trigger.&amp;nbsp; If you saturate your substrates, they'll perform poorly.&amp;nbsp; You want moisture to leave the casing or substrate/cake, etc., and then you replace it with misting.&amp;nbsp; This ebb and flow of substrate moisture is what makes mushrooms pop.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;Everyone in a cold climate should run a humidifier or two in their house all winter while running the heat.&amp;nbsp; We keep a large kettle of water boiling on the wood stove all winter.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>13727580</next>\n<prev>13726974</prev>\n<first>13726722</first>\n<last>13730210</last>\n<when>1294125155</when>\n<utime>01/04/11 09:12 AM</utime>\n</post>"}